Data Scientist		SNAP Interactive, Inc.		New York		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>Do you want to work for a top tech company in New York? Do you want to become part of a fast-growing company with a great culture full of passionate and enthusiastic people?  Then join SNAP! </p><p>  </p><p>We are looking for an analytical savant to take our data and develop strategies that will improve our product, our business and the experience for our 25+ Million Facebook-connected members. This is an excellent opportunity to contribute to contribute to a data-driven, meritocratic tech company with a goal to eliminate loneliness in the world.       </p><p></p><p><strong><span style="text-decoration:underline">Responsibilities:</span></strong> </p><ul><li>Monitor multiple simultaneous A/B tests to determine effectiveness   </li><li>Leverage our Splunk analytics tool to delve into the behavior of our different members </li><li>Monitor key metrics and report on potential opportunities/problems </li><li>Make recommendations based on data to improve how we make decisions at SNAP </li><li>Work closely with developers, product managers and CEO to develop product solutions </li><li>Model out potential product ideas to determine potential</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>SNAP Interactive, a publicly traded company based in New York City, creates leading and cutting-edge social dating products. Snap's flagship product, AYI (AreYouInterested?) is one of the largest social dating applications on the internet with over 75 million installs, and offers a completely integrated Facebook, iPhone, Android and Web app. SNAP also recently launched The Grade, a mobile dating application catering to high quality singles, that has been featured in TIME, Fortune magazine, New York Post, ABC News, USA Today, Fox News, and others. </p><p> </p></div>